prefix:
O, call not me to justify the wrong
That thy unkindness lays upon my heart;
Wound me not with thine eye but with thy tongue;

hypotheses:
In my thoughts.
The wisdom of my self is that of mine own;
For I shall not blame my own folly;
Nor shall thou live with my faults and tears.
  Be true and true to thyself,
  When thou dost express sorrow and hate.
  I am all things, all those who love thee;

prefix:
In faith, I do not love thee with mine eyes,
For they in thee a thousand errors note;
But 'tis my heart that loves what they despise,
